      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>That makes sense. When you talk about those \"primitive\" or traditional kinship-based structures, do you think those societies are just an earlier stage of development that modern civilizations eventually grow out of? Like, is it a natural progression from those simpler ways of living toward the more complex ones we see now?",
